# How the Mila's API work

## Rental approvals

Before a real estate owner can lease their lot (also called a real estate unit) and take out rental insurance, they must
first submit a rental approval request to Mila Customer Service. The rental approval request includes information
regarding the lot, the tenant and their professional situation, their revenues, etc. If the request is approved, Mila
Customer Service will provide the real estate owner with a certificate attesting that the tenant’s professional
situation and revenues are in line with Mila’s requirements.

Below are described the objects used for rental approval creation
![rental approval creation description](https://assets.service.mila.care/external-broker-api/post-approval-en.png)

For rental approval création [POST /brk/v1/{reaId}/rental-approvals](#tag/Rental-approvals/operation/create)
For rental approval
Update [PUT /brk/v1/{reaId}/rental-approvals/{approvalId}](http://localhost:8888/#tag/Rental-approvals/operation/update)

---
**NOTE**

It is important to note that all the above objects (lot, owner, tenant) have Mila’s Technical IDs which need to be
stored in the Partner’s system. This way when the Partner needs to create a rental-approval with information that was
already communicated to Mila (e.g. to rental-approvals for the same lot and owner but with different tenants), they
should only communicate Mila’s Technical IDs of the objects that are already present in Mila’s System, in this case, the
lot and owner, so that the creation of duplicates in Mila’s System is avoided (Duplicates can make the processing of
rental approvals more time-consuming, and will impair Mila’s ability to answer their clients in a timely fashion)

---

Request sample :

```json
{
  "parent_policy": {
    "id": 3
  },
  "business_data": {
    "real_estate_lot_usage": "HOME_AND_PROFESSIONAL",
    "sitting_tenant": false,
    "rent": 500,
    "charges": 50,
    "rent_including_charges": 550,
    "deposit": 500,
    "currency": "EUR",
    "furnished": true,
    "payment_splitting_mode": "MONTHLY"
  },
  "fleet_element_entities": [
    {
      "entity": {
        "id": 28
      },
      "business_role": "RISK"
    },
    {
      "entity": {
        "id": 33
      },
      "business_role": "OWNER"
    },
    {
      "entity": {
        "id": 40
      },
      "business_role": "OWNER"
    },
    {
      "entity": {
        "id": 35
      },
      "business_role": "TENANT",
      "professional_situation": {
        "id": 17
      },
      "related_fleet_element_entities": []
    },
    {
      "entity": {
        "id": 36
      },
      "business_role": "TENANT",
      "professional_situation": {
        "id": 24
      },
      "related_fleet_element_entities": [
        {
          "entity": {
            "id": 37
          },
          "business_role": "SURETY",
          "professional_situation": {
            "id": 19
          },
          "related_fleet_element_entities": []
        },
        {
          "entity": {
            "id": 38
          },
          "business_role": "SURETY",
          "professional_situation": {
            "id": 19
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Definition of used data:

| Data                   |                        |                                |    | Definition                                                                                                         | Required | Type    |
|------------------------|------------------------|--------------------------------|----|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------|---------|
| parent_policy          |                        |                                |    | Rentral insurance Group Policy to which the rental-approval will be attached (and subsequently the child policy)   | true     | object  |
|                        | id                     |                                |    | Technical ID of the Group Policy                                                                                   | true     | integer |
| business_data          |                        |                                |    | Informations relating to the lease                                                                                 | true     | object  |
|                        | real_estate_lot_usage  |                                |    | Is the lot used for housing purposes, for commercial purposes or both ?                                            | true     | enum    |
|                        | sitting_tenant         |                                |    | Is the tenant already in the lot ?                                                                                 | true     | decimal |
|                        | rent                   |                                |    | Rent amount as agreed in the lease, without charges                                                                | true     | decimal |
|                        | charges                |                                |    | Charges included in the lease (for example garbage disposal, etc.)                                                 | true     | decimal |
|                        | rent_including_charges |                                |    | Rent amount including charges                                                                                      | true     | decimal |
|                        | deposit                |                                |    | Security deposit (used for example, by the owner in case of degradation in the lot)                                | false    | decimal |
|                        | currency               |                                |    | Currency in which the rent is payed (only EUR is accepted)                                                         | true     | enum    |
|                        | household_type         |                                |    | Household type described the situation in which the tenant(s) is(are) : e.g. Single, Married, etc.                 | false    | enum    |
|                        | furnished              |                                |    | Is the lot rented with furniture provided by the owner or not ?                                                    | true     | boolean |
| fleet_element_entities |                        |                                |    | List of entities playing a role in the rental-approval                                                             | true     | array   |
|                        | entity                 |                                |    |                                                                                                                    | true     | object  |
|                        |                        | id                             |    | Technical ID of the entity                                                                                         | true     | integer |
|                        |                        | business_role                  |    | Role played by the entity in the rental-approval                                                                   | true     | enum    |
|                        |                        | professional_situation         |    | Used for the tenants to determine if they are working with a fixed contract, if they are retired, unemployed, etc. | true     | object  |
|                        |                        |                                | id | Technical ID of the Professional situation                                                                         | true     | integer |
|                        |                        | related_fleet_element_entities |    | Additional information provided only for the tenants in some cases                                                 | false    | array   |
|                        |                        | additional_incomes             |    | Additional income streams that the tenant can use                                                                  | false    | array   |
|                        |                        |                                | id | Technical ID of the Additional incomes                                                                             | true     | integer |
